## CRITICAL: Matching Activity Structure (activity_matching)

**Draggable items:**
- Class: `activity-item` with varied color backgrounds for visual distinction
- Attribute: `data-activity-item="item-1"` - REQUIRED (use "item-1", "item-2", etc.)
- Attribute: `data-aria-id` - REQUIRED for accessibility
- Attribute: `data-id="text-id"` - REQUIRED for translation
- Attribute: `draggable="true"` - REQUIRED for drag functionality
- Attribute: `tabindex="0"` - REQUIRED for keyboard navigation
- Attribute: `aria-label` - REQUIRED describing the item
- Color variety: Use `bg-yellow-100`, `bg-teal-100`, `bg-pink-100`, `bg-orange-100`, `bg-blue-200`, `bg-green-100`, etc.

**Drop zones with images:**
- Class: `dropzone border border-gray-300 p-4 rounded-lg text-center` - REQUIRED
- Attribute: `data-aria-id` - REQUIRED for accessibility
- Attribute: `aria-label` - REQUIRED describing what should be dropped
- Attribute: `tabindex="0"` - REQUIRED for keyboard navigation
- Contains: `<img>` with proper `data-id` and `data-aria-id` attributes
- Contains: `<div id="dropzone-N" role="region" aria-live="polite" class="border-t border-gray-200 mt-4 pt-2"></div>` - REQUIRED
  where N is a sequential number (1, 2, 3...)

**Layout structure:**
- Two column layout: draggable items on left, dropzones with images on right
- Responsive: `flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4`
- Items container: `grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-1 gap-4 text-center`
- Dropzones container: `grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4`

Example matching activity:
```html
<section data-section-type="activity_matching" role="activity" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto" aria-labelledby="main-heading">
  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 mb-6 md:items-start">
    <!-- Draggable items -->
    <div class="grow grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-1 gap-4 text-center">
      <div class="bg-yellow-100 p-3 rounded-md shadow-sm activity-item"
           data-activity-item="item-1"
           data-aria-id="aria-30-2-0"
           data-id="text-30-17"
           draggable="true"
           tabindex="0"
           aria-label="Palabra bimotor"
           id="bimotor">bimotor</div>
      <div class="bg-teal-100 p-3 rounded-md shadow-sm activity-item"
           data-activity-item="item-2"
           data-aria-id="aria-30-2-1"
           data-id="text-30-18"
           draggable="true"
           tabindex="0"
           aria-label="Palabra bibliobús"
           id="bibliobus">bibliobús</div>
      <!-- More items... -->
    </div>

    <!-- Drop zones with images -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-gray-300 p-4 rounded-lg text-center dropzone"
           data-aria-id="aria-30-2-6"
           tabindex="0"
           aria-label="Zona para soltar imagen de bicolor"
           id="target1">
        <img src="images/30_img-30-7.png"
             alt="Ilustración de una bandera de colores verde y rojo"
             class="w-auto h-24 mx-auto"
             data-id="img-30-7"
             data-aria-id="aria-30-2-7" />
        <div id="dropzone-1" role="region" aria-live="polite" class="border-t border-gray-200 mt-4 pt-2"></div>
      </div>
      <!-- More dropzones... -->
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-6 text-center">
    <p id="feedback" class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold" aria-live="polite"></p>
  </div>
</section>
```

**Key requirements:**
- Use `activity-item` class for draggable items
- Each item needs unique `data-activity-item="item-N"` identifier
- Each item needs `data-id` matching text ID from content
- Each dropzone needs unique `id="dropzone-N"` identifier
- Images in dropzones must have `data-id` matching image ID from content
- All elements need proper ARIA labels and accessibility attributes
- Use varied background colors for visual distinction
- Feedback area at bottom for activity results
